  "body": "## Kintsugi 🍵 milestones\r\n\r\nRef: https://notes.ethereum.org/@djrtwo/kintsugi-milestones\r\n\r\n- [x] M0: Implementation started\r\n- [x] M1: Spec Implemented https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/pull/3418\r\n- [x] M2: 1-to-1 Interop – One EL and one CL team pair off for basic interop testing (:heavy_check_mark:  Geth, :heavy_check_mark:   Nethermind)\r\n- [x] M3: Many-to-Many Interop – 2 or more EL and CL teams perform interop testing\r\n- [x] M4: Weekly devnet – Weekly devnet build for more in depth testing (https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/3452)\r\n- [x] M5: All-to-All persistent testnet – All ready EL and CL teams create a long-lived devnet first week of december\r\n- [ ] M6: Kintsugi🍵 code released – lients release Kintsugi🍵 code for public consumption\r\n\r\n## Kintsugi 🍵 TODO\r\n\r\nSpec versions https://hackmd.io/@n0ble/kintsugi-spec\r\n\r\n- [x] Consensus specs PR to implement. See https://github.com/ChainSafe/lodestar/issues/3076\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2617\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2621\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2682\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2683\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2684\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2686\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2687\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2698\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2699\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2711\r\n- [x] #3483\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2720\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2728\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2738\r\n  - [x] https://github.com/ethereum/consensus-specs/pull/2719\r\n- [x] Polish optimistic sync, only attest and build blocks on fully verified execution payloads\r\n  - Very helpful resources [Optimistic Sync Homepage](https://hackmd.io/Ic7VpkY3SkKGgYLg2p9pMg)\r\n  - [Optimistic Sync: Which is the right head for the job?](https://hackmd.io/xsk9_feiQ3SIYz2yRa1z7Q)\r\n\r\n----\r\n\r\n![360_F_395687776_8reIYev9jpL6l3hvKCWMdTbIgbCQr05p](https://user-images.githubusercontent.com/35266934/140315365-bbab8196-5dfc-4663-86e5-1ddce46f7215.jpg)\r\n\r\n> Kintsugi is the unique and traditional Japanese art of repairing broken, chipped and cracked pottery using lacquer and gold.\r\n",
